    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-07-15T11:32:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-07-15T11:32:00-05:00" n="639"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d639">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">884A.00 TA/6–2653:Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 639<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Israel</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-07-15T12:32:00-04:00"
                            >July 15, 1953—12:32 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>41. Joint State–<gloss target="#t_DMS1">DMS</gloss> message. Reference <gloss
                        target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 1965.<note n="1" xml:id="d639fn1">
                        <ref target="#d631">Document 631</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>We are disturbed by implications <persName corresp="#p_EL1"
                            >Eshkol</persName> remarks, particularly re intention continue borrowing
                        as much as possible. Would appreciate your comments as to (a) extent they
                        represent considered views Israel Government generally, (b) relationship
                            <persName corresp="#p_AE1">Avriel</persName> resignation, which seems
                        most regrettable, to any change in climate official opinion. You may wish
                        inquire Foreign Office whether policy <pb facs="1297" n="1257"
                            xml:id="pg_1257"/> expressed paragraph 5 (a) Israel Embassy’s note
                        August 11, 1952<note n="2" xml:id="d639fn2">Not printed.</note> has been
                        modified or abandoned.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>We concur basic discussions on financial problems should take place Tel
                        Aviv and are pointing out to Israel Embassy (a) while we are always prepared
                        listen to Embassy any subject, if Israel Government wishes its views be
                        promptly and fully considered in preparation recommendations on which
                        Department and <gloss target="#t_DMS1">DMS</gloss> primarily rely, it is
                        essential that it initiate and concentrate financial-economic discussions
                        Tel Aviv; (b) $6,000,000 emergency release was withheld until mission
                        considered problem and made recommendations. You are authorized so inform
                        Israel Government.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>Re your comment prevention Israel default next fiscal year may require
                        bulk of grant appropriation, we request you give priority attention to
                        preparation estimate sum which would be required this purpose. <gloss
                            target="#t_USG1">USG</gloss> does not consider itself committed
                        guarantee <gloss target="#t_IG1">IG</gloss> against default, and you may
                        inform Foreign Minister in your discretion that <gloss target="#t_IG1"
                            >IG</gloss> might make serious mistake if it assumes U.S. will
                        henceforward act to prevent default. Department concurs Embassy observation
                        that effects loss of 1954 program goods on economy must be carefully weighed
                        against consequences default.</item>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SHE1">Stassen</persName> will inform Israel Ambassador
                        that application Export-Import Bank loan for funding purposes would not
                        receive U.S. Government support, as careful study Tel Aviv and here
                        indicates such loan not appropriate for U.S. Government lending institution.
                        Israel would accordingly be well advised seek private arrangements re
                        debt.</item>
                    <label>5.</label>
                    <item>As simultaneous notification Israel Foreign Office decision Para 4 might
                        strengthen your position, you will be informed prior to actual notification
                        here in order to make possible concurrent notification in your discretion.
                        Suggest you consider possible advantages informing Foreign Office with
                        Ministry Finance officials present rather than informing <persName
                            corresp="#p_EL1">Eshkol</persName> group alone.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF2">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
